data.message:
improve LED finder (#189)

if the single pixel that is most changed has NANs,
don't immediately throw out the sample

fix: don't append observations if finder has failed

Without this patch, the observations array size is increased by 2 even when
`findInternal()` returns `false`.

The following patch would have solved the problem too, but it seemed
cleaner to let `findInternal()` work on a temporary copy instead of
tracking down and undoing all changes:

    @@ -208,6 +208,9 @@ ROS_INFO_STREAM("looking for point " << i);
               isnan(rgbd.point.z))
           {
             ROS_ERROR_STREAM("checkerboard_finder: NAN point on geometrymsgs point " << i);
    +
    +	// undo the resize from above
    +        msg->observations.resize(msg->observations.size() - 2);

             return false;
           }
